# Continuous Delivery (Jez Humble & David Farley)

Focus on how integration tests ensure code is "deployable". Applicable to pipeline (Bamboo, scripts) and Forge deployment.

- **Deployment Pipeline**: check-all.sh should be guardian of main branch.
- **Automated Acceptance Tests**: Verify Product Owner acceptance criteria are met.
- **Ephemeral Environments**: Try to make integration tests create and destroy their own "universe".
- **Smoke Testing**: A fast integration test verifying Forge app "turns on".
- **Build Once, Deploy Many**: Tested code should be exactly the same as deployed.
- **Configuration Management**: Test how app behaves with different Forge variables.
- **Zero Downtime**: Plan tests verifying compatibility between app versions.
- **Versioned Database**: (Storage schema).
- **Feedback Loop**: Test result should reach developer in seconds.
- **Stop the Line**: If integration test fails, nobody pushes code until fixed.
- **Test Security**: Integration to verify unauthorized user receives 403.
- **Load and Performance**: Integration tests measuring memory consumption in Forge runtime.
- **Rollback Testing**: Verify you can go back if data change goes wrong.
- **Use Blue-Green Deployments** (in Forge environments context).
- **Centralize Test Logs.**
- **Test Error Recovery.**
- **Automate EVERYTHING.**
- **Use "Binary Artifacts".**
- **Responsibility Segregation in Pipeline.**
- **Measure "Test Debt".**
